You are working on the Elamrit marketing site (Astro + Tailwind).

## Goal
- Keep the site **premium and effortless to read**.
- Prefer clarity + touch-target usability without losing the elegant, letterspaced brand voice.

## Typography baseline
- **Body copy SHOULD** land around **16–18px** equivalent baseline.
- **Paragraph leading SHOULD** be ~**1.6–1.8** for long-form readability.
- **Avoid “pretty but tiny” type**: anything below ~**12–13px** is allowed only for decorative micro-labels and must remain legible.

## Navigation & footer
- **Nav link text MUST NOT** be smaller than typical UI body text.
- **Dropdown menus MUST** be comfortably readable (avoid app-like tiny sizes).
- **Footer fine print SHOULD** use muted color/weight, not tiny text; it must remain readable at a glance.

## Hierarchy (preferred knobs)
When you need hierarchy, use these tools in this order:
1) **Color/opacity**
2) **Weight**
3) **Spacing**
4) **Size** (last — don’t shrink below readability thresholds)

## Letterspacing & uppercase
- Uppercase + tracking is part of the brand voice, but:
  - If tracking is high, **increase font-size slightly** (or reduce tracking).
  - When raising size, **reduce tracking** to avoid a “shouty” look.

## Buttons & CTAs
- **CTA text MUST** be readable without zooming; don’t rely on tracking alone.
- **CTA hit targets SHOULD** be comfortably tappable (aim ~40px+ effective height where possible).

## Components vs one-off styling
- Repeated patterns **SHOULD** become variants in:
  - `src/components/ui/button-variants.ts`
  - `src/components/ui/card-variants.ts`
- Avoid pasting long one-off Tailwind class strings across many components; prefer shared variants + `src/styles/app.css` patterns.

## Accessibility quick checks
- Muted text is fine, but **contrast MUST** stay legible against the background.
- Primary interactive elements **SHOULD** be usable with touch and mouse (comfortable spacing and target size).
